<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1938-01-24T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1938-01-24T20:00:00-05:00" n="140" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d140">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">711.008 North Pacific/271: Telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Ambassador in Japan</hi> (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Grew</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-01-24T20:00:00-05:00">January 24, 1938—8
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>24. Your 51, January 24, 4 p.m., paragraph 1. The Department approves of
                            your leaving with the Minister for Foreign Affairs following your
                            representations an informal memorandum containing the text of Section 1
                            of the Department’s 20, January 22, 3 p.m., and headed “orally
                            presented” to be understood as for the strictly confidential use of the
                            Foreign Minister.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>